        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="switch-info-a" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#006600;" value="A: NO - The switch only breaks the +5V line." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="25" width="340" x="1540" y="215" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="switch-info-detail" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;" value="Why: When the switch opens (OFF position), it&#xa;disconnects +5V from the circuit. There&#39;s no voltage&#xa;present to &#39;dump&#39; anywhere. The circuit simply has&#xa;no power.&#xa;&#xa;GND remains connected at all times - this is safe&#xa;and standard for DC power switching." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="95" width="340" x="1540" y="245" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
